name: RedDoorz Plus @ Mahendradatta Denpasar
address: Jl. Buana Raya No.100xx, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1:
It was horrible ! The worst hotel i went to. We didn't stay the all trip. We didn't get a refund as well !!!!
It was not clean, smell like cigarettes.....
review 2:
This is my second time i stayed here. The first time was awesome, room is nice, comfortable and clean.

Recently i visited this place again, hoping i could find the same hotel i used to stay, but it changed so much. First, they asked me to pay additional 50k a day because i requested room with two beds (they also told us that room with two beds only available in the first floor). So we paid the additional 50k but they still gave us room with only one bed. We tried to complain but the receptionist gave no response, they finally let me move to the two beds room around 8pm.

The second room was a lil bit smelly, the light is also dirty :') the bathroom equipments are rusty (like in the pic). After two days staying in that room, the AC water was leaking caused water puddle everywhere. We finally moved to the other room.

Me and my brother expected to swim there, but we discouraged ourselves because the pool was dirty as hell, the water is green and there were so many trash under the pool floor (u guys are lucky that i lost the pool photos)

The only thing that i like staying here is bcoz there's a lot of street food outside, halal food also.

Am i coming back to this hotel? Definitely no :) +50k additional charged made this stay even more not worth it. Sorry guys, u used to be my favorite but u have disappointed me so much :)

Update: there's actually a photo to show that the pool was green, this hotel is so Lucky i dont have that dirty trash photo of the pool
review 3: the location is located in the heart of city. you only need couple of minutes to reach your destination. i chose this hotel because its location. no breakfast is OK. since you can take out your breakfast/lunch/dinner.
review 4: Cozy place, cheap, peacefully and very recommended to stay. The staffs are kind too. You can see the good view in 3rd floor at midday. There's place for eat in front of hotel like meatball and warteg. Located in Mahendradatta, Denpasar city
review 5: Very bad room, very bad service, very bad condition in toilet, all very bad. I never go back in there

name: Valoma Guest House
address: 85MM+C7H, Gg. Fujiyama, Padangsambian Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80117, Indonesia
review 1: Booked two nights, and when we arrived the place looked closed down. While we waited for a call back from the reception (as there wasn't anyone there) we had a look around... The pool was green, dirt and dust everything, ladders and stuff lying around! Nothing like the pictures. The room looked okay through the window but after looking around we had already decided not to stay. Take a look at the pictures and make your own mind up... I guess lockdown wasn't so kind on this place!
review 2: Quiet nice place for stay around Padangsambian. Affordable price but the access to this hotel little bit bad. The facility I think need to be upgrade. Like provide more water for the customer as long as they stay at the hotel, no toothbrush, the towel is not that clean
review 3:
Thr guesthouse is located at the end of a small road in a quiet area with lots of local people. The next supermarket is about 10min walk away, but there are many warungs in the neighbourhood.
Very friendly owners, who are 24/7 there to help you out. The breakfast was nice, especially the smoothies :)
The room is clean and cozy. They have wifi, but the signal is not that strong in the rooms.
review 4:
Tucked in the very end of the lane down the road, still it keeps a beautiful tiny secret inside. Though, you will doubt it when you first see it, you can't of course see it from the front of the gate.

Nice staff, nice owner, the breakfast is good, it's worth for money to come here.
review 5: Nice housekeeper that available if you need him almost 24 hours, clean bedsheet and towels with shampoo and liquid soap amenities, though I bought another soap bar because their soap and shampoo made my skin and hair dry. Location is away from noises and many local 'warung' along the street. A nice food stall would need 15 minutes walking and you have to google the way. Wifi dead while I stayed for 3 days 2 night, pantry not cleaned properly, bathroom and wastafel need paid attention with cleaning details. Wifi dead was a big problem for me since the signal inside my room is rather poor so I have to open my window that face to the neighbourhood to get some signal and finished my work.

name: Tata's Pudding
address: x ( depan spbu, Jl. Buana Raya No.47, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80118, Indonesia
review 1:
Stunning tasting puddings with equally nice drinks, with service to match.

I stumled across this shop as I had an hour to kill between meetings.

The presentation of the food and shop itself are as impressive as each other.

With only 8 seats in the shop, which could easily accommodate 5 tables of 4 people, it is clearly aimed at the wholesale and takeaway market. I'd still take the time out to pop in and sit down in the shop to experience the quality of their puddings.

The service was so friendly and helpful, too.

I ate the Klopertart Ori Mini which cost Rp 15,000 (¬£0.75). This was a vanilla tasting custard with a few sultanas and almonds, I think. Stunning taste.

The drink was one of their 3 Silky Drinks. I chose the Korean banana milk. It had a layer of chocolate at the bottom which broke into lumps which seemed strange at first, but tasted nice.
review 2: So in love with their product. But unfortunately the Vla's a little bit watery. Price are slighty pricey, the staffs are SUPER FRIENDLY, the have promos every weeks and the rest are very good
review 3: Always been our favorite pudding since long time ago! And they always innovative with the new menu. Yummy and highly recommended‚ù§Ô∏è

name: Adhya Apartments
address: Jl. Bikini No.30, Padangsambian Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
I recently had the pleasure of staying at Adhya Apartments for four months, and it was an absolute dream. The room itself was comfortable and inviting, providing a perfect haven to relax after exploring the beauty of Bali.  An added bonus was the well-equipped kitchen within the room. This allowed me to prepare meals at my leisure, which was perfect for those nights I wanted to unwind and dine "in."

However, the true highlight of my stay was the pool. It was expansive and impeccably clean, offering a refreshing escape on hot days. Whether I was seeking a morning dip to wake up or an evening cool-down, the pool never failed to impress.

Overall, my stay at Adhya Apartments was nothing short of idyllic. I highly recommend it to anyone seeking a comfortable and refreshing home base in Bali, with the convenience of preparing their own meals.

name: Ratih Bali Hostel
address: Jl. Buana Raya Jl. Mahendradata Gg. Buana Dwipa No.4A, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1: I really enjoyed my stay at the place, particularly the soothing sounds of birds in the morning. Although I couldn't identify the specific bird species, I noticed there were hanging cages on the first floor. The location is convenient, with plenty of nearby food options. The staff was friendly and kind. The old-fashioned house evokes a sense of traditional Balinese architecture, and the small balcony on the third floor offers a lovely view of the surroundings. I especially liked the charming little windows. Waking up to the enchanting melodies of birds in the early morning was truly mesmerizing and a delightful treat for the ears.
review 2: very nice hostel and amazing host. Only stayed for one night after my flight to get some rest, but definitely recommend it!
review 3:
Best hostel in Denpasar hands down! The owner made this place feel like home away from home, very kind and helpful. He helped me plan my travels in Bali and recommended places to visit and stay.
As for the hostel itself, the rooms are clean and the AC works well. The beds are quite big for singles and comfortable. There's free coffee and tea and breakfast is included. It's surprisingly beautiful on the inside, and the two terraces have nice views.
The location is perfect if you want to feel like a local as it's in an area with barely any tourism. This means that everything surrounding the hostel is local, the street food is delicious and cheap and you can walk around without getting hassled by street vendors like in the more popular areas of the city (looking at you, Kuta).
Overall, great hostel to explore Denpasar from away from the crowds and with the nicest management in town. Thank you for a great couple of days.
review 4: This hostel is a very nice stay. It the rooms are clean and the toilettes are also ok. The host was very sympathic. We got a great meal at the morning the one night we stayed
review 5: Loved the squacky birds, so funny. Best hostel I had been in Bali, in fact the whole of Indonesia. Owner was an absolute top bloke, didn't speak a lick of English but he knew some sign language. Great view of the local yutes from the rooftop.

name: Bakso Urat Mercon Buana
address: Bakso mercon malang, Jl. Buana Raya No.93, Padangsambian, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80119, Indonesia
review 1:
I recently had the pleasure of dining at Bakso Urat Mercon Buana, and it was a truly fiery and flavorful experience that left a lasting impression. This humble eatery exceeded my expectations in terms of taste, quality, and overall dining experience.

The star of the show at Bakso Urat Mercon Buana is undoubtedly their signature dish, the "mercon" meatball. These meatballs pack a punch with their intense spiciness, providing a thrilling culinary adventure for those who enjoy spicy flavors. The combination of tender beef and a fiery kick creates a unique and unforgettable taste that sets this place apart from other bakso establishments.

Apart from the fiery meatballs, the overall flavor profile of the dishes at Bakso Urat Mercon Buana is exceptional. The broth is rich and flavorful, infused with aromatic herbs and spices that tantalize the taste buds. Each bite is a burst of savory goodness, showcasing the mastery and expertise of the kitchen.

The attention to detail in the preparation of the dishes is also worth mentioning. The meatballs are handmade with care, ensuring a consistent texture and quality. The accompanying condiments, such as fried shallots, chili sauce, and lime, complement the meatballs perfectly, enhancing the overall taste experience.

In terms of service, Bakso Urat Mercon Buana excels. The staff members are friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the menu. They are always ready to provide recommendations and accommodate any special requests. The prompt and efficient service contributes to a pleasant dining experience, making customers feel welcomed and valued.

Despite being a small and unassuming eatery, the cleanliness and hygiene standards at Bakso Urat Mercon Buana are commendable. The dining area is well-maintained, and the kitchen practices proper sanitation, giving customers peace of mind when enjoying their meal.

In conclusion, Bakso Urat Mercon Buana is a hidden gem for food enthusiasts seeking a fiery and flavorful culinary adventure. From the intense spiciness of the mercon meatballs to the overall quality of the dishes, this eatery stands out as a must-visit for those who appreciate bold flavors and exceptional taste. With friendly service and a commitment to cleanliness, Bakso Urat Mercon Buana delivers a delightful dining experience that is sure to satisfy even the most discerning palates.
